TEHRAN , March 26 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Iranian Army have busted two Afghan drug rings and killed seven traffickers near Iran 's eastern borders , a military officer said here on Sunday .
The rapid deployment divisions of the infantry also seized nine kilograms of opium and seven firearms from the drug traffickers in the encounter on Saturday , the Islamic Republic News Agency -LRB- IRNA -RRB- reported .
The infantry divisions have been deployed along 900 kilometers of Iran 's eastern borders with Afghanistan and Pakistan since September 1998 following the tension mounted between Iran and the Afghan Taliban militia .
The Taliban forces stormed the Iranian consulate general in Mazari Sharif in August 1998 and killed eight Iranian diplomats and an IRNA reporter inside it after the militia took over the stronghold of the anti- Taliban Northern Alliance .
Iran is a main transit route for drugs smuggled from Afghanistan , the world 's largest opium producer , and neighboring Pakistan to Europe and oil-rich Gulf Arab states .
Earlier this month , a security force commander said that Iran had seized 240 tons of various drugs in the last Iranian calendar year which ended on March 19 .
